1. Extract files to a web-accessible directory
2. Create a MySQL user and schema, import the SQL schema using `mysql -u <user> -p < lib/flickr.sql`
3. Create a Flickr API key: https://www.flickr.com/services/apps/create/
4. Put your keys and passwords in lib/credentials.default.php and move the file to lib/credentials.php
5. Open your browser to the install location
6. Create your user login
7. Create a cron job to run cron.php every 6 hours (or more often if you like poking the Flickr bear)
   */6 *  * * *  nobody php /path/to/scrapr/cron.php
8. Create search queries and follow users through the app's settings